definition.value: A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of 2-octadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl group is specified as octadecanoyl (stearoyl).
A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of Phe-Ala; major species at pH 7.3.
A peptide cation obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy terminus and protonation of the side-chain guanidino group and the amino terminus of Phe-Arg; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of chromanes that is gamma-CEHC in which the phenolic hydrogen is replaced by a beta-glucuronosyl residue.
A dicarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of at least one of the carboxy groups of gamma-CEHC beta-glucuronide.
A monounsaturated fatty aldehyde that is undecanal which has undergone formal dehydrogenation to introduce a double bond at unspecified position.
A carbohydrate derivative that is beta-cyclodextrin in which some of the hydroxy groups have been methylated.
A bromo fatty acid that is hexadecanoic (palmitic) acid carrying a single bromo substituent at position 2.

A styrylquinoline that is trans-2-styrylquinoline in which the the phenyl group has been substituted at position 2 by a hydroxy group. It is an anti-angiogenic compound that exerts a dose-dependent antagonism of the cysteinyl leukotriene pathway, preferentially antagonising cysteinyl leukotriene receptor 1. The major species at pH 7.3
An N-acylhexadecasphingosine-1-phosphocholine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).
A medium-chain fatty acid that is decanoic acid substituted at position 2 by a hydroxy group.
An undecenal in which the C=C bond is located at the 2-3 position.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxydecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A bile acid glycine conjugate having hyocholic acid as the bile acid component.
A cholanic acid conjugate anion that is the conjugate base of glycohyocholic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 6-ketopiperidine-2-carboxylic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An ornithine derivative in which one of the amino hydrogens on the side-chain of ornithine has been replaced by an acetyl group.
An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of N(5)-acetylornithine; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acetyl-L-amino acid that is N-acetyl-L-histidine in which the hydrogen attached to position 1 on the imidazole ring has been replaced by a methyl group.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-acetyl-1-methyl-L-histidine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acetyl-L-amino acid that is N-acetyl-L-histidine carrying a methyl substituent at position 3 on the imidazole ring.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-acetyl-3-methyl-L-histidine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of pyrrolidin-2-ones in which the amide hydrogen of pyrrolidin-2-one has been replaced by a 3-acetamidopropyl group.
An aryl sulfate that is 2-aminophenol in which the phenolic hydrogen has been replaced by a sulfo group.

A pyridinemonocarboxylic acid that is nicotinic acid which is substituted at position 2 by a 4,5-dihydro-imidazol-2-yl group, which in turn is substituted at positions 4, 4, and 5 by isopropyl, ethyl, and oxo groups, respectively.
A 2-(4-isopropyl-4-methyl-5-oxo-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-2-yl)nicotinic acid that has R configuration.
A 2-(4-isopropyl-4-methyl-5-oxo-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-2-yl)nicotinic acid that has S configuration.
A compound that inhibits the oxidation of any fatty acid.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of (R)-imazapyr.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of (S)-imazapyr.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of (S)-imazamox.
A phenylsulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 2-aminophenyl hydrogen sulfate, obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxyibuprofen, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is ibuprofen in which the methine proton on the isobutyl group has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
A dicarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of at least one of the carboxy groups of carboxyibuprofen.
A dicarboxylic acid that is ibuprofen in which one of the methyl groups in the isobutyl portion has been converted to the corresponding carboxylic acid.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of carboxyibuprofen.
A tetrasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-GlcA-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Xyl in which the reducing end hydroxy hydrogen has been replaced by a benzyl group.
A generic representative substrate in the ADP ribosylation of proteins
A generic representative product of ADP ribosylation of proteins
A glycosylxylose derivative that is beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Xyl in which the anomeric hydroxy hydrogen has been replaced by a benzyl group.
A carbohydrate acid derivative anion that is the conjugate base of trans-3-hydroxycotinine beta-D-glucuronide, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A beta-D-glucosiduronic acid that is trans-3-hydroxycotinine in which the hydroxy hydrogen is replaced by a beta-D-glucuronyl residue.
An N-acylindole that is N-acetylindole carrying an additional formyl substituent at position 3.
An N-glycosylzeatin that is cis-zeatin having a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue attached at position N-9.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of bisorcic, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-glycosylzeatin that is trans-zeatin having a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue attached at position N-9.
An N-glycosylzeatin that is cis-zeatin having a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue attached at position N-7.
